HEADWORD: Ewe-necked
<hw>Ewe"-necked`</hw> <pr>(⟦umac⟧"n⟦ecr⟧kt`)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<def>Having a neck like a ewe; -- said of horses in which the arch of
the neck is deficient, being somewhat hollowed out.</def>
<rj><au>Youwatt.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

